Press Releases.Title: 1 New Case of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 10 February 2021, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed 1 new case of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. Based on our investigations so far, the case resides in a dormitory and there are no new cases in the community. 

2.       In addition, there are 14 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. In total, there are 15 new cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore today.

3.       We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
10 FEBRUARY 2021
